1 Section 1. Chapter 363C of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2, 3 and 4 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. “Consumer price inflation index” means the Consumer Price Index
4 for All Urban Consumers, West Region (All Items), as published by the United
5 States Department of Labor or, if that index ceases to be published by the United
6 States Department of Labor, the published index selected by the Department of
7 Taxation pursuant to subsection 11 of NRS 361.091.
8 Sec. 3. “Revenue threshold” means the amount described in subsection 1
9 of section 4 of this act for a given taxable year.
10 Sec. 4. 1. The revenue threshold is:
11 (a) For the taxable year beginning on July 1, 2025, $4,000,000 plus the
12 product of $4,000,000 multiplied by the average 12-month percentage increase in
13 the consumer price inflation index for the 3 calendar years immediately
14 preceding the taxable year beginning on July 1, 2025. The revenue threshold
15 calculated pursuant to this paragraph must be rounded to the nearest $100,000.
16 (b) For each subsequent taxable year:
17 (1) If the average 12-month percentage change in the consumer price
18 inflation index for the 3 calendar years immediately preceding the taxable year
19 for which the revenue threshold is being calculated is positive, the revenue
20 threshold for the immediate preceding taxable year plus the product of the
21 revenue threshold for the immediately preceding taxable year multiplied by the
22 average percentage increase in the consumer price inflation index for the 3
23 calendar years immediately preceding the taxable year for which the revenue
24 threshold is being calculated. A revenue threshold calculated pursuant to this
25 subparagraph must be rounded to the nearest $100,000.
26 (2) If the average 12-month percentage change in the consumer price
27 inflation index for the 3 calendar years immediately preceding the taxable year
28 for which the revenue threshold is being calculated is negative, an amount equal
29 to the revenue threshold for the immediately preceding taxable year. A revenue
30 threshold calculated pursuant to this subparagraph must be rounded to the
31 nearest $100,000.
32 2. [On or before March 1 of each year,] Not later than 30 days after July 1,
33 2025, the Department shall calculate and publish on its Internet website the
34 revenue threshold for the taxable year that began on July 1, 2025. Not later than
35 March 1 of each subsequent year, the Department shall calculate and publish on

